cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY 

This paper is about data-driven robotics, which involves using machine learning techniques to enable robots to perform tasks based on data rather than explicit programming. The paper focuses on using a large dataset of recorded robot experience to learn reward functions and train robot policies offline using batch RL. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves using computer vision (cs.CV) to perceive the environment and control systems (cs.SY) to control the robot. Finally, the paper also involves using artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques to learn the reward function and train the robot policy.
